            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-05-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="275" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Angel</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Seward</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">[Extract.]</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 76.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Stockholm</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 22, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>The Swedish law is very strict against the violation of the rights of neutrals,
                    and I am assured that there is no apprehension that any of the ports of this
                    kingdom or of Norway will he prostituted to the wicked purpose of fitting out
                    privateers.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with much respect, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>B. F. ANGEL.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
